        <item>
            <title>2.9.0</title>
            <pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 12:54:29 +0900</pubDate>
            <link>https://github.com/Saqoosha/Canopy</link>
            <sparkle:version>74</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>2.9.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>15.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description sparkle:format="markdown"><![CDATA[### Features
- Multi-pane split view: open 2-5 sessions side-by-side. Cmd+click a sidebar row to add a pane; Cmd+Opt+←/→ navigates between panes; Cmd+W closes the focused pane; Cmd+1..9 focuses the Nth pane. Window grows/shrinks with pane add/close; per-pane title bar with hover-only close X. Drag the divider to redistribute pane widths.
- Per-model rate-limit bars in the sidebar: a fixed-column "Usage" section shows each model's weekly bucket (Fable, Sonnet, etc.) alongside the 5-hour and 7-day account bars, with progressive color thresholds.
- Pane-drag scroll-preserve: chat stays pinned to the newest message when you resize a pane or the window.

### Changes
- Per-pane status bar now collapses responsively at narrow widths (drops session usage, CLI version, branch, then context numeric in a fixed priority order; a popover keeps the model badge).
- Rate-limit bars in the sidebar were softened (subtler colors) and gained a CodexBar-style pace tick.
- Extension version moved to the sidebar footer; pane-footer separators cleaned up.
- Launcher's Recents no longer shows managed git worktrees.
- Pane divider is now hover-cursor discoverable (thin separator line) after the accent-color focus border was removed.

### Bug Fixes
- Empty session on resume for sessions whose worktree directory was relocated.
]]></description>
